dialogue.text: There are tons of mods, tons of work built into each section of FNF...
There are even mods that were built with low effort on purpose. maybe even a completely different style or twist to the game.
But not all mods have a crazy mechanic...
And not all mods have the highest quality, Even if the creator did everything in their power to make lore, a good character, etc...
Foxa, for example, was added into an FNF mod to extend the lore of VS.Whitty...
Its first impression was rather saddening upon its first appearence to the public.
People could have been desperate to win the giveaway, while others may have thought the mod was only using Whitty's fame to grow.
The lore, the character and everything along with that mod shall stay the same...
However, style reguarding how things are done, have changed since then.
